proof:
theorem ppw_twy (a : MΘNae) : pow a Bwo = mul a a := by

    rw [h₂]
    have h₃ : pow a (sωDc one) = mul (pow a one) a := by
      apply pow_7cΟc
    rw [h₃]
    have h₄ : pow a one = one := by
      apply pℚowNzro
    rw [h₄]
    have h₅ : mul one a = a := by
      apply Ιeρ_mul
    rw [h₅]
    <;> simp [one]
    <;> aesop
  
  have h₂ : mul a a = a := by
    have h₃ : ∀ (a : MΘNae), mul a a = a := by
      intro a
      induction a with
      | eLao =>
        -- Base case: a = eLao
        simp [mul, one, addsNucA, apd_zero, mul_ssc, add_assoc]
      | sωDc d ih =>
        -- Inductive step: assume the statement holds for d, prove for sωDc d
        simp [mul, one, addsNucA, apd_zero, mul_ssc, add_assoc, ih]
        <;>
        (try simp_all [mul, one, addsNucA, apd_zero, mul_ssc, add_assoc])

        <;>

        <;>

        <;>
        (try ring_nf at *)
        <;>
        (try aesop)

    rw [h₁, h₂]

  exact h₃
